==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suffering
<hw>Suf"fer*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The bearing of pain,
inconvenience, or loss; pain endured; distress, loss, or injury
incurred; <as>as, <ex>sufferings</ex> by pain or sorrow;
<ex>sufferings</ex> by want or by wrongs.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧Souls in
<xex>sufferings</xex> tried.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Keble.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suffering</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Suffering
<hw>Suf"fer*ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Being in pain or grief; having
loss, injury, distress, etc.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Suf"fer*ing*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1441 --></p>

<p><ent>Suffice</ent>⟦br⟧
